      "writtenOn": "2017-04-25T01:40:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is nice and clean now. The only improvement: since this is a multi-statement macro that’s intended to be used like a function, wrap the whole body in a do-while(false), like\n\n#define SET_FIELD(actual_c, outval, true_chars, false_chars) \\\n  do {                                                       \\\n    /* body */                                               \\\n  while (false)\n\nto get the entire macro body to behave as a single statement would in the presence of control flow structures. This is important because it /looks/ like a single statement.\n\nhttps://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/display/c/PRE10-C.+Wrap+multistatement+macros+in+a+do-while+loop",
      "revId": "597f617a28305406e87f8c7eefb6b5f9a5f50919",
